0Nick%20Jonas%20enjoyed%20a%20stylish%20dinner%20date%20in%20London%2C%20captivating%20fans%20with%20their%20chic%20looks%20on%20social%20media.%20The%20couple%20was%20seen%20stepping%20out%20in%20relaxed%20attire%20that%20perfectly%20balanced%20comfort%20and%20style.%20Nick%20opted%20for%20a%20casual%20hoodie%20paired%20with%20cargo%20pants%2C%20while%20Priyanka%20chose%20an%20oversized%20light%20blue%20shirt%20complemented%20by%20gray%20pants.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20Entertainment%20Desk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fpriyanka-chopra-and-nick-jonas-shine-in-casual-chic-during-dinner-date-in-london-pics-inside%2Farticleshow%2F114693365.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20Endorsement%20Sans%20Election%3A%20How%20Indira%20Gandhi's%20Death%20Changed%20Everything%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-10%2Fp851c66_indira-gandhi_625x300_28_October_24.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EForty%20years%20ago%2C%20on%20October%2031%2C%201984%2C%20India%20saw%20a%20sudden%20change%20of%20guard%E2%80%94Rajiv%20Gandhi%20was%20sworn%20in%20as%20Prime%20Minister%20within%20four-and-a-half%20hours%20of%20the%20official%20announcement%20of%20the%20assassination%20of%20Indira%20Gandhi.%20In%201964%20and%201966%2C%20when%20the%20premiership%20changed%20following%20the%20death%20of%20a%20predecessor%2C%20new%20incumbents%20were%20sworn%20in%20after%20a%2013-day%20mourning%20period.%20But%20things%20were%20different%20in%201984.%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20and%20Lal%20Bahadur%20Shastri%20had%20died%20due%20to%20natural%20causes%3B%20Indira%20Gandhi%20had%20fallen%20to%20the%20bullets%20of%20assassins%2C%20her%20own%20bodyguards.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20planners%20of%20the%20assassination%20had%20chosen%20a%20perfect%20day%3A%20President%20Zail%20Singh%20was%20on%20a%20visit%20abroad%3B%20Cabinet%20Secretary%20Krishnaswamy%20Raosahib%20and%20the%20Prime%20Minister's%20Principal%20Secretary%2C%20P.C.Alexander%2C%20were%20in%20Bombay%20for%20a%20meeting%20of%20the%20Atomic%20Energy%20Commission%3B%20Pranab%20Mukherjee%2C%20the%20designated%20number-two%20in%20the%20Indira%20Gandhi%20Cabinet%2C%20was%20in%20West%20Bengal%2C%20accompanying%20All%20India%20Congress%20Committee%20general%20secretary%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%20on%20a%20tour%20of%20rural%20areas%3B%20Home%20Minister%20P.V.Narasimha%20Rao%20was%20visiting%20coastal%20Andhra%3B%20the%20Congress%20Working%20President%2C%20Kamlapati%20Tripathi%2C%20was%20touring%20Uttar%20Pradesh%3B%20Defence%20Minister%20Shankarrao%20Chavan%20was%20in%20Moscow%2C%20leading%20a%20delegation%20of%20Army%20and%20Air%20Force%20top%20brass%3B%20Naval%20chief%20Admiral%20Dawson%20was%20in%20Vishakhapatnam%3B%20and%20top%20intelligence%20advisor%2C%20Ram%20Nath%20Kao%2C%20was%20abroad.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EDark%20Days%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThanks%20to%20the%20resilience%20of%20India's%20democracy%2C%20chaos%20was%20avoided%20and%20a%20smooth%20transition%20of%20power%20ensued%2C%20though%20it%20was%20blotted%20by%20the%20bloodshed%20of%20anti-Sikh%20riots%2C%20for%20which%20ultra-enthusiasts%20of%20the%20ruling%20party%20were%20blamed%20(some%20are%20facing%20trial%20to%20date).%20It%20was%20a%20macabre%20period%E2%80%94apparently%2C%20voters'%20lists%20and%20ration%20card%20addresses%20had%20been%20used%20to%20identify%20Sikh%20homes%20for%20the%20pogrom.%20Indira%20Gandhi's%20assassination%20was%20an%20aftermath%20of%20Operation%20Bluestar%2C%20in%20which%20the%20Army%20flushed%20out%20terrorists%20by%20attacking%20Amritsar's%20Golden%20Temple%20complex.%20She%20was%20killed%20by%20Sikh%20bodyguards%20in%20her%20home%2C%201%20Safdarjung%20Road.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20norm%20and%20form%20were%20bypassed%20on%20that%20fateful%20day.%20It%20set%20in%20motion%20a%20departure%20from%20the%20observance%20of%20custom%20and%20ushered%20in%20an%20era%20of%20ad%20hoc%2C%20off-the-cuff%20decision-making%20in%20the%20Congress%2C%20in%20which%20the%20long%20shadow%20of%20bureaucracy%20and%20advisors%20(read%3A%20family%2C%20friends)%20over%20seasoned%20political%20leadership%20was%20all%20too%20evident.%20Palace%20intrigues%20were%20not%20new%20to%20the%20Grand%20Old%20Party.%20But%20in%201984%2C%20it%20was%20endorsed%20and%20institutionalised.%20Pigmies%20began%20dwarfing%20stalwarts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EConstitution%20And%20'Acting%20PM'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201964%20and%201967%2C%20the%20charge%20of%20interim%20Prime%20Minister%20fell%20on%20the%20shoulders%20of%20Home%20Minister%20Gulzari%20Lal%20Nanda.%20India%20has%20no%20Constitutional%20provision%20for%20having%20an%20%E2%80%98acting%20Prime%20Minister'.%20Yet%2C%20Nanda%20was%20sworn%20in%2C%20ultimately%20demitting%20office%20after%20the%20next%20Prime%20Minister%20was%20formally%20chosen%20by%20the%20Congress%20Party%20in%20Parliament%20(CPP).%20Party%20president%20K.%20Kamraj%20orchestrated%20the%20candidatures%20of%20Lal%20Bahadur%20Shastri%20in%201964%20and%20Indira%20Gandhi%20in%201966.%20On%20both%20occasions%2C%20conservative%20right-wing%20leader%20Morarji%20Desai%20lost%20out%E2%80%94he%20would%20become%20the%20Janata%20Party%20Prime%20Minister%20in%201977.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201984%2C%20Indira%20Gandhi%20herself%20was%20Congress%20President.%20She%20had%20appointed%20Kamlapati%20Tripathi%20as%20the%20Working%20President.%20On%20the%20day%20of%20her%20assassination%2C%20he%20was%20on%20tour.%20Thus%2C%20unlike%20in%201964%20and%201966%2C%20there%20was%20no%20%E2%80%9CKamraj%E2%80%9D%20available%20in%20New%20Delhi.%20On%20both%20of%20those%20previous%20occasions%2C%20President%20Sarvepalli%20Radhakrishnan%20was%20at%20the%20Rashtrapati%20Bhavan%20to%20mentor%20and%20monitor%20succession.%20In%201984%2C%20Gyani%20Zail%20Singh%20was%20on%20a%20visit%20to%20Yemen%20(he%20rushed%20back%20upon%20hearing%20the%20news).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Announcement%20Of%20Gandhi's%20Death%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20Indira%20Gandhi's%20bullet-ridden%20body%20lay%20at%20the%20All-India%20Institute%20for%20Medical%20Sciences%20(AIIMS)%2C%20a%20conference%20room%20was%20opened%20up%20for%20ministers%20and%20senior%20bureaucrats.%20Indira%20Gandhi's%20longtime%20aide%2C%20R.K.%20Dhawan%2C%20was%20also%20there%2C%20but%20the%20eclipsing%20of%20his%20status%20was%20all%20too%20evident.%20The%20advisor%20in%20the%20Prime%20Minister's%20Secretariat%2C%20Vijay%20Shankar%20Tripathi%2C%20a%20retired%20IAS%20officer%2C%20acting%20in%20tandem%20with%20Rajiv%20Gandhi's%20buddies%2C%20called%20the%20shots.%20He%20advised%20Principal%20Information%20Officer%20U.C.%20Tiwari%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20news%20was%20not%20officially%20announced%20by%20%3Cem%3EAkashvani%3C%2Fem%3E%20till%206%20pm%2C%20though%20doctors%20had%20announced%20her%20death%20at%202.20%20pm.%20Information%20minister%20H.K.L.%20Bhagat%20was%20kept%20out%20of%20the%20loop%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20news%20had%20been%20broadcast%20by%20%3Cem%3EBBC%20%3C%2Fem%3ELondon%20around%2011%20am%2C%20soon%20after%20the%20Indira%20Gandhi%20family's%20yoga%20teacher%2C%20Dhirendra%20Brahmachari%2C%20came%20out%20of%20the%20eighth-floor%20operation%20theatre%2C%20where%20Gandhi's%20body%20lay%2C%20and%20said%20with%20a%20strange%20wave%20of%20the%20hand%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Eab%20sab%20Bhagwan%20ke%20haath%20mein%20hai%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D%20(now%20it's%20in%20the%20hands%20of%20the%20Almighty).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20the%20%3Cem%3EBBC%20%3C%2Fem%3Ebroadcast%2C%20most%20Indian%20missions%20abroad%20had%20lowered%20the%20national%20flag%20to%20half-mast.%20US%20President%20Ronald%20Reagan's%20condolences%20reached%20New%20Delhi%20at%202%20pm%20(even%20before%20the%20medical%20bulletin).%20However%2C%20as%20per%20Tripathi's%20diktat%2C%20Indira%20Gandhi%20was%20%E2%80%98officially%20alive'%20till%206%20pm.%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%20was%20sworn%20in%20at%206.55%20pm.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERajiv%20Gandhi%20had%20heard%20the%20news%20put%20out%20by%20%3Cem%3EBBC%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethat%20forenoon%20on%20a%20transistor%20radio%20in%20a%20village%20in%20Midnapore%20district.%20Pranab%20Mukherjee%20was%20by%20his%20side.%20He%20decided%20to%20rush%20back%20to%20Delhi.%20A%20special%20Indian%20Airlines%20flight%20was%20arranged%20from%20Calcutta.%20Mukherjee%20and%20another%20minister%2C%20A.B.A.%20Ghani%20Khan%20Choudhary%2C%20accompanied%20him.%20He%20reached%20AIIMS%20at%203.40%20pm.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%20Became%20PM%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERajiv%20Gandhi%20was%20of%20the%20opinion%20that%20a%20senior%20minister%20should%20hold%20the%20fort%20till%20things%20were%20finalised%20by%20the%20CPP.%20But%20this%20was%20not%20to%20be%2C%20as%20Parliamentary%20Affairs%20Minister%20Buta%20Singh%2C%20AICC%20treasurer%20Sitaram%20Kesari%2C%20Arun%20Nehru%20and%20Rajiv%20Gandhi's%20school%20friend%20and%20aide%2C%20Arun%20Singh%2C%20were%20on%20the%20same%20page%20as%20V.S.%20Tripathi%3B%20a%20signature%20campaign%20endorsing%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%20was%20already%20on.%20The%20Youth%20Congress%20had%20announced%20that%20if%20anyone%20else%20was%20sworn%20in%2C%20%26quot%3Bthere%20would%20be%20trouble%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPresident%20Zail%20Singh%20arrived%20at%20AIIMS%20at%205%20pm.%20His%20motorcade%20had%20been%20pelted%20with%20stones%20as%20he%20drove%20from%20the%20Palam%20airport%20(anti-Sikh%20riots%20had%20engulfed%20the%20nation).%20During%20a%20conversation%20he%20had%20with%20this%20writer%20in%20August%201985%2C%20Singh%20recalled%20the%20day's%20events%20thus%3A%20on%20learning%20that%20Indira%20Gandhi%20had%20been%20shot%2C%20he%20decided%20to%20return%20from%20Yemen.%20He%20asked%20his%20Secretary%2C%20IAS%20officer%20A.C.%20Bandopadhyay%2C%20to%20get%20a%20copy%20of%20the%20Constitution%20from%20the%20local%20Embassy.%20On%20board%20the%20IAF%20special%20aircraft%2C%20the%20President%20enquired%20about%20Rajiv%20Gandhi's%20whereabouts.%20IAF%20security%20advised%20that%20as%20the%20flight%20was%20traversing%20airspace%20adjacent%20to%20Pakistan%2C%20only%20radio%20traffic%20related%20to%20flight%20logistics%20was%20advisable%3B%20the%20President's%20mind%20should%20not%20be%20disclosed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHonouring%20Indira%20Gandhi's%20'Wish'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAfter%20studying%20the%20Constitution%2C%20I%20realised%20that%20though%20the%20President%20is%20bound%20by%20aid%20and%20advice%20of%20the%20Cabinet%20headed%20by%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20he%20has%20one%20independent%2C%20unfettered%20power%3A%20to%20choose%20who%20ought%20to%20be%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20and%20swear%20him%20in%2C%E2%80%9D%20Singh%20added.%20He%20said%20he%20owed%20his%20position%20to%20Indira%20Gandhi%20and%20wished%20to%20fulfil%20her%20wish%20that%20her%20son%20should%20be%20her%20successor.%20On%20reaching%20AIIMS%2C%20he%20put%20his%20arm%20around%20Rajiv%20Gandhi's%20shoulders%20and%20invited%20him%20to%20the%20Rashtrapati%20Bhavan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20selection%20of%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%20was%20done%20during%20a%20meeting%20of%20the%20Congress%20Parliamentary%20Board%20(CPB)%2C%20%C2%A0an%20organisational%20apex%20body%2C%20and%20not%20by%20CPP%2C%20the%20parliamentary%20wing.%20Of%20the%20five-member%20CPB%2C%20only%20two%20people%E2%80%94Pranab%20Mukherjee%20and%20P.V.%20Narasimha%20Rao%E2%80%94attended.%20Kamlapati%20Tripathi%20and%20Margatham%20Chandrashekhar%20were%20not%20in%20Delhi.%20The%20decision%20of%20the%20CPB%20was%20conveyed%20to%20the%20President%20in%20a%20handwritten%20note%20signed%20by%20the%20AICC%20General%20Secretary%20(Organisation)%2C%20G.Karuppiah%20Moopanar%20(as%20a%20prot%C3%A9g%C3%A9%20of%20Kamraj%2C%20Moopanar%20had%20witnessed%201964%20and%201966%20successions%20from%20the%20sidelines).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%20was%20being%20sworn%20in%20at%20the%20Rashtrapati%20Bhavan's%20Durbar%20Hall%2C%20a%20meeting%20of%20the%20CPP%20was%20being%20held%20in%20Parliament's%20Central%20Hall.%20It%20was%20presided%20by%20its%20deputy%20leader%2C%20Prof.%20N.G.%20Ranga%2C%20who%20was%20oblivious%20to%20the%20developments%20in%20the%20Rashtrapati%20Bhavan.%20Thirty%20members%20attended.%20A%20condolence%20resolution%20was%20adopted.%20The%20CPP's%20endorsement%20was%20post%20facto%3A%20on%20November%202%2C%20a%20resolution%20was%20passed%20with%20497%20out%20of%20505%20votes%20(eight%20MPs%20were%20absent)%20%E2%80%98electing'%20the%20new%20Prime%20Minister.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThus%2C%20a%20new%20era%20began.%20Endorsement%20of%20leadership%2C%20and%20not%20election%2C%20became%20the%20norm.%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%20won%20the%20ensuing%20General%20Election%20by%20a%20record%20score%2C%20surpassing%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20and%20Indira%20Gandhi.%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5CnFive%20years%20later%2C%20beginning%201989%2C%20Congress%20stopped%20getting%20a%20Lok%20Sabha%20majority%20on%20its%20own.%20The%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%2C%20born%20on%20April%206%2C%201980%2C%20contested%20its%20first%20election%20on%20the%20lotus%20symbol%20in%201984%2C%20winning%20a%20mere%20two%20seats.%20Decades%20later%2C%20in%202014%2C%20it%20would%20emerge%20as%20India's%20party%20of%20governance%20with%20a%20clear%20mandate.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Shubhabrata%20Bhattacharya%20is%20a%20retired%20editor%20and%20a%20public%20affairs%20commentator)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1730116140000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-10%2Fsp0tddo8_indira-gandhi_625